headline: W.R. Berkley Q4 Earnings Miss Estimate, Revenues Up Y/Y
summary: W.R. Berkley posted solid full-year growth as higher premiums and record investment income offset a Q4 earnings miss and elevated expenses.

headline: Greg Abel Signals Shift as Berkshire Weighs Kraft Heinz Exit?
summary: BRK.B may exit its Kraft Heinz stake in Greg Abel's first major move, signaling a shift from Buffett's legacy.

headline: Brown & Brown Q4 Earnings Top Estimates on Strong Investment Income
summary: BRO's Q4 results reflect higher commission and fees, improved investment income, and higher adjusted EBITDAC, offset by lower organic revenues.
